# MegaLinter .trivyignore
#
# All entries below document CVEs that trivy flags inside MegaLinter Docker
# images but that are not exploitable in the way MegaLinter actually uses
# the affected tool. The common reasoning across most entries:
#
#  - Every linter runs as a short-lived CLI process in CI, against files
#    in the user's workspace. No tool starts a network server, exposes
#    an authenticated API, or processes attacker-controlled traffic.
#  - DoS-class vulnerabilities (ReDoS, parser DoS, infinite loops) cost
#    a CI minute at worst; there is no live service to take down.
#  - Path-traversal vulnerabilities only matter if untrusted paths cross
#    the API boundary — in CI the workspace path is trusted.
#  - Most "fixed version" entries with a `Remove when X upgraded to Y`
#    comment can be deleted once renovate ships the upgrade.

# --- .NET SDK / runtime ---
# CVEs in the .NET SDK/runtime used by Roslynator, devskim, etc.
# MegaLinter loads .NET only to invoke static analyzers on local source
# files; no ASP.NET hosting, no untrusted assembly load, no network IO.
CVE-2024-0057
CVE-2024-30105
CVE-2024-38095
CVE-2024-38168
CVE-2024-43483
CVE-2024-43484
CVE-2024-43485
# https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/2025/cve-2025-26646/
# MSBuild spoofing requiring crafted project files from an attacker;
# MegaLinter only builds and analyzes the repo's own .NET projects.
CVE-2025-26646

# --- containerd ---
# CVEs in containerd embedded by some Docker tooling. MegaLinter runs
# inside a container; it never starts containerd or accepts container
# spec input from outside the CI workflow.
# https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2024-25621
CVE-2024-25621
# https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-52881
CVE-2025-52881
# https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-46680 — containerd user ID handling
# bypass allows runAsNonRoot evasion. Embedded in the grype, syft and trivy
# binaries which are used as static scanners only; they never run containers
# or evaluate runAsNonRoot policy. Remove when upstream tools rebuild against
# containerd >=2.2.4 / >=2.3.1 (or >=1.7.32 for the v1 line).
CVE-2026-46680
# https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-53488 — containerd CRI image-config LABEL
# injection. https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-53489 — arbitrary host CRI log
# file read via symlink following. https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-53492 —
# CRI checkpoint restore CDI annotation smuggling. All three require a running
# containerd CRI server; the containerd embedded in the grype/syft/trivy scanner
# binaries is used as a static-analysis library only and never serves CRI.
# Remove when upstream tools rebuild against containerd >=2.3.2.
CVE-2026-53488
CVE-2026-53489
CVE-2026-53492

# --- Docker (moby) ---
# CVE-2024-41110: AuthZ plugin bypass in moby. MegaLinter never runs a
# Docker daemon inside its containers, and AuthZ plugins are not
# configured — bypass has nothing to bypass.
CVE-2024-41110

# --- Devskim (.NET) ---
# Pre-2020 .NET Core HTTP/socket-stack CVEs that ship with the .NET
# runtime trivy fingerprints. Devskim parses regex rules locally, no
# HTTP/socket usage in MegaLinter's invocation.
CVE-2018-8292
CVE-2019-0820

# --- Go stdlib (all Go-based linters) ---
# Most Go linters (actionlint, dustilock, gitleaks, kubeconform,
# ls-lint, protolint, revive, shfmt, terraform, terragrunt, terrascan,
# tflint, grype, syft, trivy, etc.) ship statically linked against a
# specific Go toolchain version. Each new Go release brings stdlib
# CVEs that trivy reports against every embedded binary, even when the
# affected stdlib package is unreachable.
# Across these tools: no HTTP server, no TLS termination, no DNS
# resolution of attacker-controlled hostnames, no email parsing,
# no HTML rendering.
CVE-2024-6257
CVE-2023-45288
CVE-2024-24788
CVE-2024-24790
CVE-2024-45337
CVE-2024-45338
CVE-2025-22869
