CVE-2025-22871
CVE-2025-22874
CVE-2025-30204
CVE-2025-47906
# https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/2025/cve-2025-47907/ — net/http data race
CVE-2025-47907
# net/http transport DoS
CVE-2025-47912
CVE-2025-58183
CVE-2025-58185
CVE-2025-58186
CVE-2025-58187
CVE-2025-58188
# https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-58189 — crypto/tls ALPN handshake error leak; linters do not accept inbound TLS
CVE-2025-58189
CVE-2025-61723
CVE-2025-61724
# https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-61725 — net/mail ParseAddress domain-literal DoS; linters do not parse email addresses
CVE-2025-61725
CVE-2025-61726
# https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-61727 — crypto/x509 excluded subdomain constraint bypass; linters perform no certificate validation
CVE-2025-61727
CVE-2025-61728
CVE-2025-61730
CVE-2025-68121

# --- go-git ---
# Path/permission bypasses in go-git embedded by several Go linters.
# MegaLinter only ever passes the local workspace to git_diff and the
# scanners; no remote URLs or hostile repositories are cloned.
CVE-2025-21613
CVE-2025-21614

# --- Java PMD (used by sfdx-scanner and code-analyzer) ---
# CVE-2024-7254: ProtocolBuffers Java parser DoS via deeply-nested
# untrusted protobuf input. PMD analyses local Apex/Java source code
# and never deserialises external protobuf payloads.
CVE-2024-7254
# GHSA-2r2c-cx56-8933 / GHSA-47qp-hqvx-6r3f: JLine3 Telnet server
# unauthenticated remote DoS and remote memory exhaustion.
# jline-3.21.0.jar is bundled in usr/bin/pmd/lib for PMD's interactive
# shell; PMD runs as a CLI static analyzer and never starts the JLine
# Telnet server. Remove when PMD upgrades its bundled jline to >=4.2.1.
GHSA-2r2c-cx56-8933
GHSA-47qp-hqvx-6r3f

