# go-git CVE-2026-45022: improper parsing of malformed git commit/tag objects
# affecting commit signature verification. Affected tools at their latest
# releases (kubescape v4.0.8, grype v0.112.0, syft v1.44.0, trivy v0.70.0)
# still pin go-git v5.17.x/v5.18.0. Not applicable as all four are used as
# static scanners on local files and do not parse attacker-controlled git
# objects or perform commit signature verification. Remove when upstream
# tools upgrade to go-git >=5.19.0.
CVE-2026-45022
# go-billy CVE-2026-44973: path traversal in osfs.ChrootOS when attacker-
# controlled paths are passed. In MegaLinter these tools run as local
# static scanners and do not expose go-billy filesystem APIs to untrusted
# external input. Affected: kubescape v4.0.8, grype v0.112.0, syft v1.44.0,
# trivy v0.70.0, terragrunt alpine 1.15.2. Remove when upstream tools
# upgrade to go-billy >=5.9.0 / >=6.0.0-alpha.1.
CVE-2026-44973

